I think this is the right next artifact. If the Operator Kernel is Pantheon’s “instruction set,” then the Compiler is the thing that turns intent into execution.

Pantheon Compiler v1.0

Mission → Leverage Pipeline

⸻

Purpose

The Pantheon Compiler transforms human intent into executable, measurable, and reusable workflows.

It performs for missions what a software compiler performs for source code.

Human intent is the source language.

Execution is the machine language.

⸻

Core Invariant

Every mission can be progressively transformed into a sequence of observable actions while preserving its underlying objective.

The Compiler does not determine the mission.

The Compiler determines how best to pursue it.

